    <description>Stems erect, branched, 1–6(–10) dm, glabrous (to sparsely farinose when young);
        proximal branches decumbent. Leaves nonaromatic; petiole 1–2.5 cm; blade triangular, ovate,
        or rhombic-ovate, 0.8–4(–8) × 0.4–3(–5) cm, base cuneate to rounded, margins irregularly
        dentate, apex acute to acuminate, glabrous (rarely indistinctly farinose when young).
        Inflorescences glomerules in terminal and lateral panicles, 6–7 × 4–5 cm; glomerules
        subglobose, 2–4 mm diam., or some flowers not in glomerules; bracts absent. Flowers:
        perianth segments 5, distinct nearly to base; lobes ovate, 0.5–0.8 × 0.6–0.7 mm, apex acute
        to obtuse, keeled abaxially, farinose, covering fruit at maturity; stamens 5; stigmas 2, 0.2
        mm. Achenes depressed-ovoid; pericarp adherent, pustulate, becoming smooth with maturity.
        Seeds lenticular, round, 1–1.5 mm diam.; seed coat black, minutely rugose to ± smooth. 2n =
        18.</description>
